comments: Abolished 1.4.1974 to become an unparished area.

Unparished area which until 1.4.1974 formed the parishes of Blackburn 
    and Darwen. See also Table 2, notes (a) and (e).

Created 1894 from the parts of the parishes of Over Darwen, Lower 
    Darwen and Eccleshill, in Darwen Municipal Borough. See also Table 2, note 
    (a).

That part which which until 1.4.1934 formed parts of the parish of Clayton-le-Dale. 
    See also Table 2, note (a).
Abolished 25.3.1893 and added to the parish of Blackburn.

Abolished 25.3.1893 and divided between the parishes of Blackburn 
    and Darwen.

Created 6.5.1975 by renaming the parish of Turton North. See also 
    Table 2, notes (d) and (e).
Abolished 1894 and added to the parish of Darwen.

That part which which until 1.4.1934 formed parts of the parish of Clayton-le-Dale. 
    See also Table 2, note (a).

Created 1.4.1974 out of the parish of Turton. Renamed 6.5.1975 
    to become the parish of North Turton. See also Table 2, note (c).
Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Blackburn.
